LAYER_0_DEFAULT.description: Use default layer (l2 Enhanced). Append 'l0' to explicitly use default intensity.

LAYER_1_NATIVE.description: Native search intensity - fast, clean results (30s timeout, 50 results/engine). Append 'l1' to query.

LAYER_2_ENHANCED.description: Enhanced search intensity - workarounds and query expansion (60s timeout, 100 results/engine). DEFAULT.

LAYER_3_BRUTE.description: Maximum recall - all variations, aggressive expansion (120s timeout, 200 results/engine). Append 'l3'.

LAYER_4_NUCLEAR.description: Brute + recursive link expansion - extracts outlinks/backlinks, scrapes all (300s). Requires scraping.
constraints: Cannot combine with t10, t20, or t30 (no-scrape tiers)

TIER_0_DEFAULT.description: Use default tier (t2 All Standard). Append 't0' to explicitly use default engines.

TIER_1_FAST.description: Fast engines only: Google, Bing, Brave, DuckDuckGo, Exa, Cymonides. Append 't1' to query.

TIER_2_ALL.description: All standard engines: T1 + Yandex, Qwant, Grok, Nature, GDELT, Aleph. DEFAULT.

TIER_3_ALL_SLOW.description: All engines + slow: T2 + Archive.org, Yep, PublicWWW. Append 't3' to query.

TIER_4_ALL_LINK.description: All engines + LINKLATER: T3 + Webgraph, Majestic, BacklinkDiscovery, GlobalLinks. Requires scraping.

TIER_10_FAST_NO_SCRAPE.description: Fast engines with raw results only (no scraping). Append 't10' to query.

TIER_20_ALL_NO_SCRAPE.description: All standard engines with raw results only (no scraping). Append 't20' to query.

TIER_30_ALL_SLOW_NO_SCRAPE.description: All + slow engines with raw results only (no scraping). Append 't30' to query.
